's production systems can only be remotely accessed by authorized employees possessing a valid multi-factor authentication (MFA) method."},{name:"Remote access encrypted enforced",description:"Resend's production systems can only be remotely accessed by authorized employees via an approved encrypted connection."},{name:"Intrusion detection system utilized",description:"Resend uses an intrusion detection system to provide continuous monitoring of the company's network and early detection of potential security breaches."},{name:"Log management utilized",description:"Resend utilizes a log management tool to identify events that may have a potential impact on the company's ability to achieve its security objectives."},{name:"Network segmentation implemented",description:"Resend's network is segmented to prevent unauthorized access to customer data."},{name:"Network firewalls reviewed",description:"Resend reviews its firewall rulesets at least annually. Required changes are tracked to completion."},{name:"Network firewalls utilized",description:"Resend uses firewalls and configures them to prevent unauthorized access."},{name:"Network and system hardening standards maintained",description:"Resend's network and system hardening standards are documented, based on industry best practices, and reviewed at least annually."},{name:"Service infrastructure maintained",description:"Resend has infrastructure supporting the service patched as a part of routine maintenance and as a result of identified vulnerabilities to help ensure that servers supporting the service are hardened against security threats."}]},{category:"Organizational Security",controls:[{name:"Asset disposal procedures utilized",description:"Resend has electronic media containing confidential information purged or destroyed in accordance with best practices, and certificates of destruction are issued for each device destroyed."},{name:"Production inventory maintained",description:"Resend maintains a formal inventory of production system assets."},{name:"Portable media encrypted",description:"Resend encrypts portable and removable media devices when used."},{name:"Anti-malware technology utilized",description:"Resend deploys anti-malware technology to environments commonly susceptible to malicious attacks and configures this to be updated routinely, logged, and installed on all relevant systems."},{name:"Employee background checks performed",description:"Resend performs background checks on new employees."},{name:"Code of Conduct acknowledged by contractors",description:"Resend requires contractor agreements to include a code of conduct or reference to the company code of conduct."},{name:"Code of Conduct acknowledged by employees and enforced",description:"Resend requires employees to acknowledge a code of conduct at the time of hire. Employees who violate the code of conduct are subject to disciplinary actions in accordance with a disciplinary policy."},{name:"Confidentiality Agreement acknowledged by contractors",description:"Resend requires contractors to sign a confidentiality agreement at the time of engagement."},{name:"Confidentiality Agreement acknowledged by employees",description:"Resend requires employees to sign a confidentiality agreement during onboarding."},{name:"Performance evaluations conducted",description:"Resend managers are required to complete performance evaluations for direct reports at least annually."},{name:"Password policy enforced",description:"Resend requires passwords for in-scope system components to be configured according to the company's policy."},{name:"MDM system utilized",description:"Resend has a mobile device management (MDM) system in place to centrally manage mobile devices supporting the service."},{name:"Visitor procedures enforced",description:"Resend requires visitors to sign-in, wear a visitor badge, and be escorted by an authorized employee when accessing the data center or secure areas."},{name:"Security awareness training implemented",description:"Resend requires employees to complete security awareness training within thirty days of hire and at least annually thereafter."}]},{category:"Product Security",controls:[{name:"Data encryption utilized",description:"Resend's datastores housing sensitive customer data are encrypted at rest."},{name:"Control self-assessments conducted",description:"Resend performs control self-assessments at least annually to gain assurance that controls are in place and operating effectively. Corrective actions are taken based on relevant findings. If the company has committed to an SLA for a finding, the corrective action is completed within that SLA."},{name:"Penetration testing performed",description:"Resend's penetration testing is performed at least annually. A remediation plan is developed and changes are implemented to remediate vulnerabilities in accordance with SLAs."},{name:"Data transmission encrypted",description:"Resend uses secure data transmission protocols to encrypt confidential and sensitive data when transmitted over public networks."},{name:"Vulnerability and system monitoring procedures established",description:"Resend's formal policies outline the requirements for the following functions related to IT / Engineering: vulnerability management; system monitoring."}]},{category:"Internal Security Procedures",controls:[{name:"Continuity and disaster recovery plans established",description:"Resend has Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery Plans in place that outline communication plans in order to maintain information security continuity in the event of the unavailability of key personnel."},{name:"Continuity and disaster recovery plans tested",description:"Resend has a documented business continuity/disaster recovery (BC/DR) plan and tests it at least annually."},{name:"Cybersecurity insurance maintained",description:"Resend maintains cybersecurity insurance to mitigate the financial impact of business disruptions."},{name:"Configuration management system established",description:"Resend has a configuration management procedure in place to ensure that system configurations are deployed consistently throughout the environment."},{name:"Change management procedures enforced",description:"Resend requires changes to software and infrastructure components of the service to be authorized, formally documented, tested, reviewed, and approved prior to being implemented in the production environment."},{name:"Production deployment access restricted",description:"Resend restricts access to migrate changes to production to authorized personnel."},{name:"Development lifecycle established",description:"Resend has a formal systems development life cycle (SDLC) methodology in place that governs the development, acquisition, implementation, changes (including emergency changes), and maintenance of information systems and related technology requirements."},{name:"Whistleblower policy established",description:"Resend has established a formalized whistleblower policy, and an anonymous communication channel is in place for users to report potential issues or fraud concerns."},{name:"Board oversight briefings conducted",description:"Resend's board of directors or a relevant subcommittee is briefed by senior management at least annually on the state of the company's cybersecurity and privacy risk. The board provides feedback and direction to management as needed."},{name:"Board charter documented",description:"Resend's board of directors has a documented charter that outlines its oversight responsibilities for internal control."},{name:"Board expertise developed",description:"Resend's board members have sufficient expertise to oversee management's ability to design, implement and operate information security controls. The board engages third-party information security experts and consultants as needed."},{name:"Board meetings conducted",description:"Resend's board of directors meets at least annually and maintains formal m